						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">FrankenGraphics wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">btw it's not all that dark for PAL. Whenever a game runs out of Vblank on NTSC is a moment where PAL excels.. provided the software doesn't forcibly cancel updates under the assumption of the Vblank being &quot;NTSC narrow&quot;.</div><br />True, but the update buffer might be sized for NTSC. In my experience, a buffer spanning the unused part of the stack page, such as $0108-$01BF, happens to be about the right size to fill NTSC vblank, and there isn't a lot of RAM in the system to store a bigger buffer. So a bigger buffer would likely need to be stored either in ROM (such as copying uncompressed tiles) or in WRAM at $6000. Where are you storing the source data for an update buffer bigger than 192 bytes?</div>

